# Prisma Design System Rules

## Core Principle
Use **only** Prisma Design System components. Never create custom UI components when a Prisma component exists.

## Components
- Always import from Prisma packages: `@prisma/components`, `@prisma/design-tokens`
- Check `design-system-docs/` before creating any component
- Custom components only for: business logic, Prisma compositions, or genuinely missing components

## Styling
- Use Prisma design tokens (colors, spacing, typography, etc.) - never hardcoded values
- Use Prisma's layout system (Box, Flex, Grid, etc.)
- Prefer Prisma utility props over custom CSS
- Custom CSS only for prototype-specific layouts or animations not in Prisma

## Imports

// ✅ Correct
import { Button, Input, Card } from '@prisma/components';
import { colors, spacing } from '@prisma/design-tokens';
import type { ButtonProps } from '@prisma/components';

// ❌ Wrong
import { Button } from '@/components/Button';
```

## Packages
- Never install: Material-UI, Ant Design, Chakra, Bootstrap, Tailwind, or similar UI libraries
- Only install: data fetching, state management, utilities, backend/API tools

## Checklist
- [ ] All UI uses Prisma components
- [ ] Design tokens for all styling values
- [ ] TypeScript types from Prisma packages
- [ ] No conflicting UI libraries

**Think "assemble" not "build"** - compose Prisma components, don't create custom UI.
